PN,39903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1773241885
OL,3,CTrial witness in wrongful rape
OL,4,Cconviction 'had no doubt' over ID -
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FMr Seward had told the jury he had
OL,8,Ftwice driven past the rape suspect who
OL,9,Fappeared to be stalking the victim in
OL,10,Fthe vicinity of Cleggs Lane in Salford
OL,11,Fshortly before the attack on 19 July
OL,12,F2003.
OL,14,FHe said he attended a digital ID
OL,15,Fparade and picked out Mr Malkinson,
OL,16,Fand at the trial told the jury he had
OL,17,F"no doubt" he was the man he saw,
OL,18,Fadding: "I picked the person I saw
OL,19,Fthat night", and that he was
OL,20,F"absolutely not mistaken".
OL,26,@yD@AOUyD@JO]zD@IOU{D@KO]|D@AOU|D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
