PN,39904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1773241885
OL,3,CTrial witness in wrongful rape
OL,4,Cconviction 'had no doubt' over ID -
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FEarlier, prosecutor John Price KC told
OL,8,Fjurors it was Quinn, not Mr Malkinson,
OL,9,Fwho had really carried out the rape,
OL,10,Feven though it was "difficult to
OL,11,Fbelieve" three people could all have
OL,12,Fidentified the wrong man.
OL,14,FOn Monday 9 March, the rape victim
OL,15,Ftold Quinn's trial she had doubts
OL,16,Fabout her identification of the rapist
OL,17,Fat Mr Malkinson's trial, but police
OL,18,Ftold her it was normal to have second
OL,19,Fthoughts and put it down to "trial
OL,20,Fnerves".
OL,26,@rD@TOUsD@HO]{D@]OU|D@GO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
